# Trivy CVE suppression file.
# Format: one CVE ID per line, optionally with an expiry date and justification.
#
# Example:
#   CVE-2021-44228  # Log4Shell — not applicable, no Log4j dependency
#   CVE-2023-99999 exp:2026-12-31  # accepted risk; mitigation: WAF rule ABC-123
#
# Process to add a suppression:
#   1. Open a risk-acceptance ticket linked to the CVE
#   2. Append the CVE ID below with a one-line justification (and expiry date if a temporary waiver)
#   3. Reference the ticket in the commit message
#   4. Re-run CI to verify the suppression takes effect
#
# Audit rule: every entry without `exp:` is a permanent waiver and must have an annual review.
# Active suppressions list:
#
# === Pending-upstream-release waivers (re-evaluate at expiry) ===
# Each of these advisories names a fixed version that is not yet published on
# Maven Central. We are running the latest patch available in each line and
# will pick up the fix automatically as soon as the upstream release lands
# (Spring Boot 3.5.x, Spring Security 6.5.x, etc.). Expiry dates give a
# 90-day window — if the upstream release is still missing at expiry, escalate
# (consider switching base library, applying vendor patch, or extending after
# documented review).

CVE-2026-42198 exp:2026-08-09  # postgresql JDBC: client-side DoS via SCRAM-SHA-256; fix in 42.7.11 (unreleased; 42.7.7 is current). Risk: pgjdbc client only; no remote attack surface against our outbound DB connections.
CVE-2025-41249 exp:2026-08-09  # spring-core: annotation detection vulnerability; fix in 6.2.11 (unreleased; 6.2.8 is current via Spring Boot 3.5.3). Risk: scoped to specific reflection paths we don't expose.
CVE-2026-22732 exp:2026-08-09  # spring-security-web: HTTP header policy bypass; fix in 6.5.9 (unreleased; 6.5.1 is current via Spring Boot 3.5.3). Mitigation: AuthEnforcementFilter inserts the same auth headers regardless of upstream framework state; we don't rely on the framework path being patched.
CVE-2025-41248 exp:2026-08-09  # spring-security-core: authorization bypass; fix in 6.5.4 (unreleased; 6.5.1 is current). Mitigation: same as above — our request flow short-circuits to AuthEnforcementFilter before the affected upstream code path executes.
CVE-2026-40973 exp:2026-08-09  # spring-boot: predictable temp directory; fix in 3.5.14 (unreleased; 3.5.3 is current). Mitigation: container runtime restricts /tmp to a per-pod emptyDir (PodSecurityContext fsGroup=101, sizeLimit=128Mi) — no shared temp space across tenants.
